From stefano.leonardi at unipr.it  Tue Jul 14 10:14:55 2015
From: stefano.leonardi at unipr.it (Stefano Leonardi)
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2015 10:14:55 +0200
Subject: [R-sig-eco] altitudinal overlap
In-Reply-To: <CAPU4_4pSwSnrYMiZ1rykp8wxKCiOHd+6OjmzeuPLW5SK2xutmA@mail.gmail.com>
References: <CAPU4_4pSwSnrYMiZ1rykp8wxKCiOHd+6OjmzeuPLW5SK2xutmA@mail.gmail.com>
Message-ID: <55A4C4FF.4000709@unipr.it>


The first think that came to my mind:

overlap <- function(v1,v2) {
ov <-min(max(v1), max(v2)) - max(min(v1), min(v2))
ifelse(ov > 0, ov, 0)
}

overlap(dat[1,], dat[2,])
[1] 0.5


Ciao
Stefano

